{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W7HiSjcriLtXKP77F4rEAu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both changes are in place and all 33 tests pass.\n\n**Summary of changes to `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`:**\n\n1. **Expanded `COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS`** (line 277) — added 50 new cooking verbs including `scatter`, `heat`, `rest`, `marinate`, `blend`, `drizzle`, `toast`, `chill`, etc. These prevent instruction-starting lines from being selected as titles.\n\n2. **Added bilingual layout pattern boost** (before threshold calculation) — when position-0 has ≤2 words, position 1-2 has a 2-5 word mixed-case non-ingredient non-instruction line, and a section label follows within 5 lines, position-0 gets a `+0.15` boost to both `score` and `thresholdScore`. This handles the \"Golonka\" / \"Roasted Pork Knuckle\" / \"Ingredients:\" pattern."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":533,"cache_read_input_tokens":35640,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":533},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"da66d640-08e5-4551-9d04-aa2649fd8c8b","uuid":"d027a8e3-db06-41c0-afa9-6bd6969c4858"}
