{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JW2RY8WFPeeLoaXx2fMCtb","type":"tool_result","content":"  1078→  // Use thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) so the structural bonus doesn't inflate\n  1079→  // the threshold and block equally-valid headings on multi-recipe pages.\n  1080→  const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n  1081→  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n  1082→\n  1083→  // Filter candidates above threshold\n  1084→  let selected = scoredForThreshold.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n  1085→\n  1086→  // Empty-pool fallback: when threshold filtering discards every candidate,\n  1087→  // the hard filters' structural verdict should not be overruled by weak\n  1088→  // embedding differentiation. Return the best positional candidate only\n  1089→  // if it has a meaningful positive raw score (avoids ingredient-list leakage).\n  1090→  if (selected.length === 0 && scored.length > 0) {\n  1091→    const fallback = scored\n  1092→      .slice()\n  1093→      .sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position || b.score - a.score);\n  1094→    // Position-0 candidates that passed hard filters are very likely titles even with\n  1095→    // weak embedding signal. Relax the rawScore guard for early-position candidates.\n  1096→    const rawScoreThreshold = fallback[0].position <= 2 ? -0.05 : 0.02;\n  1097→    if (fallback[0].rawScore > rawScoreThreshold) {\n  1098→      selected = [fallback[0]];\n  1099→    }\n  1100→  }\n  1101→\n  1102→  // Title-absent page guard: when the page starts mid-recipe (all of the first 3 non-empty\n  1103→  // lines are ingredients or cooking instructions), require a much higher rawScore and\n  1104→  // discard candidates deep in the file. This prevents stray body text or adjacent recipe\n  1105→  // titles from being picked up on pages with no title (Pattern 4).\n  1106→  if (titleAbsent) {\n  1107→    const titleAbsentThreshold = 0.10;\n  1108→    selected = selected.filter(s => s.rawScore >= titleAbsentThreshold);\n  1109→    selected = selected.filter(s => s.position <= 2);\n  1110→  }\n  1111→\n  1112→  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself survived\n  1113→  // the threshold. Cases:\n  1114→  //   ARAYES case:  firstStructuralHeading = \"ARAYES SHRAK\" (2-word join qualifies; \"ARAYES\"\n  1115→  //     alone = 1 word, so it never qualified). Filter removes \"ARAYES\" so dedup keeps the join.\n  1116→  //   SAFFRON case: baseHeading was the partial line; continuation logic above upgraded\n  1117→  //     firstStructuralHeading to the full join. Filter removes the partial so dedup keeps join.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018Pm6PsFbp7nQ4HnidkPRdZ","session_id":"da66d640-08e5-4551-9d04-aa2649fd8c8b","uuid":"ed4e2552-362f-4122-9749-fa14bee1eeaf"}
