{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0112jciHZxH6ogy4SWiYWoRs","type":"tool_result","content":"   885→    }) ?? baseHeading\n   886→  );\n   887→\n   888→  // Pass 2: apply bonuses\n   889→  const scored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; score: number; rawScore: number; baseScore: number; thresholdScore: number }> = rawScored.map((rs, candidateIndex) => {\n   890→    // Position factor: multiplicative tiebreaker — amplifies existing signal, doesn't replace it.\n   891→    // Use candidate-relative position (rank among candidates that passed hard filters) rather than\n   892→    // raw line position, so filtered preamble lines don't penalize the first real candidate.\n   893→    const candidateRelativePosition = candidateIndex / rawScored.length;\n   894→    const positionFactor = candidateRelativePosition < 0.5\n   895→      ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - candidateRelativePosition * 2)\n   896→      : 1.0;\n   897→\n   898→    // ALL_CAPS bonus: recipe books use ALL_CAPS for titles and section headings.\n   899→    // Single-word ALL_CAPS terms are overwhelmingly section/category labels, not recipe titles;\n   900→    // real recipe titles in ALL_CAPS are almost always multi-word. Reduce the bonus for single words.\n   901→    const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n   902→      ? (wordCount(rs.text) >= 2 ? 0.08 : 0.03)\n   903→      : 0;\n   904→\n   905→    // Structural heading bonus: best ALL_CAPS heading (or its continuation join) is almost always the recipe title\n   906→    const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n   907→\n   908→    // thresholdScore excludes structural bonus so the bonus doesn't inflate the threshold\n   909→    // and prevent equally-valid structural headings from passing on multi-recipe pages.\n   910→    const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n   911→    // baseScore excludes position factor — used for diagnostics and ranking\n   912→    const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   913→    const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   914→    return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n   915→  });\n   916→\n   917→  if (scored.length === 0) {\n   918→    return undefined;\n   919→  }\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018Pm6PsFbp7nQ4HnidkPRdZ","session_id":"da66d640-08e5-4551-9d04-aa2649fd8c8b","uuid":"c8a181e5-83bc-49dd-bccd-7c6a01fe22b8"}
